OL,7,FWhen you picture Spain you think of
OL,8,Fsun, sea and perhaps sangria. But in
OL,9,Fthe Pyrenees mountain range, which
OL,10,Fruns along the border with France,
OL,11,Fthere is plenty of snow and rivers of
OL,12,Fslow moving ice, known as glaciers.
OL,13,FBut for how much longer?
OL,15,FThe number of glaciers in the
OL,16,FPyrenees has fallen from 100 at the
OL,17,Fend of the 19th Century to 50 in the
OL,18,F1980s and last year just 17. They
OL,19,Fused to cover an area the size of
OL,20,F5,000 football pitches. Now, that
OL,21,Fnumber is more like 400.
OL,3,C'This is the canary in the coal
OL,4,Cmine': Scientists warn Spain's
OL,5,Cglaciers will vanish in years
